comment: I think Amber Heard or her legal team have forgotten that the burden of proof falls upon the accuser. While a civil trail and its procedures differ from a criminal trial, the burden of proof stills falls entirely upon the person or persons making the claim. While civil jury trails are not held to the same very high standard of guilt beyond a reasonable doubt that a criminal trail is but it seems as if Ms. Heard is confusing hearsay with proof. You can hear her clear misconception in her deposition and in private conversations between her and Mr. Depp. She continually tries to reexplain facts but giving her perception of what happened. In a jury trail, any attempt to impose your own opinion or explain the facts in evidence from your own point of view, its know as CALLS FOR SPECULATION and Speculation is not legally a standard for proof. In the end, any jury trail, will come down to the facts in evidence. I have no way of knowing what facts are true or untrue in this case and neither do most people, however as an obererver, Ms. Heard is short on 2 things when it comes to facts in evidence.....Facts and Evidence. Again, I can't say Mr. Depp bears no blame here but from an evidence standpoint, his case appears stronger.
author: BillyC NYC
